com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.endpoint.web

Interface WebCmsEndpointModelLoader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractWebCmsAssetModelLoader, WebCmsArticleModelLoader, WebCmsAssetModelLoader, WebCmsPageModelLoader

    public interface WebCmsEndpointModelLoader
    Beans implementing this interface will be called by the WebCmsEndpointControllerAdvice if the initial endpoint related model should be loaded. The latter is determined by the WebCmsEndpointHandlerInterceptor.

    All loader beans will be called in order until one of them returns false on the call to loadModel(HttpServletRequest, WebCmsEndpointContext, Model). Assigning a correct order to an implementation is crucial.

    Since:
    0.0.2
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    WebCmsEndpointControllerAdvice, WebCmsEndpointHandlerInterceptor

    • Method Detail

      • loadModel

        boolean loadModel(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                  WebCmsEndpointContext endpointContext,
                  org.springframework.ui.Model model)
        The return value determines if the next loader in the chain should be called. Once a loader has returned false, no other loaders will be executed.
        Parameters:
        request - responsible for loading the context
        endpointContext - loaded - will always return true on WebCmsEndpointContext.isAvailable()
        model - that can be initialized
        Returns:
        true if the next loader should still be called, false if not
